4
00:01:35,210 --> 00:01:37,020
And I ran into an old friend.

5
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:41,160
I know he came back to kill Father and avenge his family.

6
00:01:41,160 --> 00:01:42,640
I told him to leave the capital 
    

7
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:44,340
and never come back.

8
00:01:46,080 --> 00:01:49,640
Mother, did I do the right thing?

9
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:55,180
 Zhinu, come and see. 

10
00:01:55,180 --> 00:01:57,310
 It's a rare flower. 

11
00:01:57,310 --> 00:02:00,640
 When fully grown, its root and stem can be used in medicine, 

12
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:03,730
 while its flowers and seeds are poisonous. 

13
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:12,050
Who is there?

14
00:02:15,790 --> 00:02:19,180
- Second Young Master. 
 - Why are you still here?

15
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:22,300
I still have pending business to attend to.

16
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:24,120
Not afraid I'll report you?

17
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,430
I was afraid.

18
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:29,380
That's why I came to kill you today.

19
00:02:29,380 --> 00:02:32,560
- You... 
 - But I've changed my mind.

20
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:35,160
Listen.

21
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:38,070
I won't let you kill my father just because you helped me.

22
00:02:38,070 --> 00:02:40,110
You'd better give up.

23
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:44,440
What are you doing?

24
00:02:47,030 --> 00:02:49,500
Look, Second Young Master.

25
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:55,150
Is it the only flower growing on this grave?

26
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:58,710
What's so strange about flowers growing on the grave?

27
00:02:59,630 --> 00:03:03,820
Have you seen this flower anywhere in the tomb?

28
00:03:06,530 --> 00:03:09,580
This is the "Solitary South Star." The whole plant is poisonous.

29
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:11,400
Why is this poisonous plant

30
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:16,010
only growing and flourishing on your mother's grave?

31
00:03:16,010 --> 00:03:20,150
Perhaps the wind carried the seeds from somewhere else.

32
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:24,090
It's a poisonous herb unique to South Zhaozhou.

33
00:03:24,090 --> 00:03:26,490
The wind can't carry its seeds this far.

34
00:03:27,210 --> 00:03:29,150
What are you implying?

35
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:33,590
Either someone planted it on your mother's grave on purpose.

36
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:40,460
Or your mother's remains in the grave carry the seeds.

37
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:44,930
But I think you know that the former is hardly a possibility.

38
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,710
What are you implying?

39
00:03:47,710 --> 00:03:52,930
If I am right, your mother died from this poison.

40
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:58,030
That's impossible, my mother died from illness.

41
00:03:58,030 --> 00:04:00,750
I never left her side for a second before she died.

42
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:03,160
No one could have poisoned her.

43
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:06,840
The Solitary South Star may not be as toxic as arsenic,

44
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:09,530
but with a little intake of its poison every day,

45
00:04:09,530 --> 00:04:12,710
the toxin will accumulate in the organs over the years.

46
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:16,560
Eventually, the victim dies.

47
00:04:17,390 --> 00:04:19,360
If you want the truth,

48
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:24,700
all you need to do is exhume your mother's remains.

49
00:04:26,970 --> 00:04:29,440
You want me to dig up my mother's grave?

50
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:33,680
Don't you want to know the truth?

51
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,510
Perhaps the one who poisoned her

52
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:39,460
is the very person you revere and trust the most.

53
00:04:40,870 --> 00:04:43,000
Zang Hai, you're an animal!

54
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,700
What are you implying?

55
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:48,280
You're saying that my father killed my mother?

56
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:51,260
Nothing is impossible in this world.

57
00:04:51,260 --> 00:04:54,270
You want to dig up my mother's grave and kill my father.

58
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:56,310
You fabricate lies to achieve your goal.

59
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:57,800
You are insane!

60
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:59,190
Then tell me.

61
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:03,040
Why are the Zhuang family's ancestors buried in the southeast of the mausoleum

62
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:07,370
while your mother is buried on the north side alone with such a plain grave?

63
00:05:07,370 --> 00:05:10,080
Why haven't they moved her memorial tablet into the ancestral hall?

64
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:12,230
Shut up!

65
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:20,430
Most importantly, your mother's been gone for years.

66
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:23,470
Why has your father never once visited her grave?

67
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,280
Why?

68
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,700
Ask someone you know.

69
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:51,430
See if this flower is poisonous, like I said.

70
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:16,650
If you don't believe it is toxic,

71
00:06:16,650 --> 00:06:19,470
do you dare to eat it?

72
00:06:37,580 --> 00:06:40,850
I won't believe a word you say.

73
00:06:40,850 --> 00:06:43,510
I'll give you one last chance.

74
00:06:43,510 --> 00:06:46,290
Get out of my face!

75
00:06:46,290 --> 00:06:48,560
During tomorrow's ancestral rites,

76
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:54,960
open your eyes and see for yourself whether I'm telling the truth.

77
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:26,640
 Aim. 

78
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:33,310
 Shoulders relaxed. Hands steady. 

79
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:35,410
 Exhale slowly. 

80
00:07:35,410 --> 00:07:37,530
 Shoot. 

81
00:07:37,530 --> 00:07:38,970
 I hit the bull's-eye. 

82
00:07:38,970 --> 00:07:41,340
 Well done, Xing'er! 

83
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:45,470
 Have some water. 

84
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:53,390
 Mother, you promised to make me nut-filled pastries tonight if I hit the bull's-eye. 

85
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:55,620
 What a little foodie. 

86
00:07:55,620 --> 00:07:58,120
 Will you not practice if I don't make you food? 

87
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:02,090
 This kid's got the same guts I had back in the day. 

88
00:08:02,090 --> 00:08:06,740
 The next general in the family will be him. 

89
00:08:06,740 --> 00:08:09,630
 Make sure he practices riding and archery every day. 

90
00:08:09,630 --> 00:08:10,520
 Don't let him slack off. 

91
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:13,120
 I can't lead troops like you. 

92
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:15,310
 How can I shoulder such a responsibility? 

93
00:08:15,310 --> 00:08:17,060
 Please teach him yourself. 

94
00:08:17,060 --> 00:08:19,130
 All right. Keep going. 

95
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:49,630
My Lord. My Lady.

96
00:08:49,630 --> 00:08:51,750
The carriages are ready.

97
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:56,040
The servants are already preparing the incense and offerings at the mausoleum.

98
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,550
   

99
00:08:57,550 --> 00:08:59,600
Have you brought all the hunting stuff?

100
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,930
Yes. Rest assured, My Lady.

101
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:04,150
Father.

102
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:05,870
You got up early today.

103
00:09:05,870 --> 00:09:09,080
I dare not be late for the ancestor veneration.

104
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:10,740
Good to know.

105
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:14,960
I don't see Official Zang today.

106
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,320
Isn't he coming?

107
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,960
He wasn't feeling well last night and asked for leave.

108
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,650
Let's set off.

109
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:24,470
- Anything else? 
 - I...

110
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:28,530
Zhixing, let's not miss the hour for the ancestral rites.

111
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:32,440
- We can talk on the way... 
- Zhixing.

112
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,670
I have business to discuss with Father.

113
00:09:34,670 --> 00:09:37,730
Why don't you wait until we arrive?

114
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:05,630
Sandalwood's fragrance lingers, pure and long.

115
00:10:05,630 --> 00:10:10,350
Steadying the state, our ancestors' virtue is strong.

116
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:43,290
Jade cups hold fine wine, like amber's glow.

117
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:47,870
With cleansed hands we drink, their grace to show.

118
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:15,830
My honored ancestors, your unworthy descendant, Zhuang Luyin,

119
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:18,450
brought his family here to pay homage.

120
00:11:18,450 --> 00:11:22,600
The family is thriving, my wife is virtuous, and my sons are filial.

121
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,790
May your noble spirits guard our way.

122
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:27,780
Pay respect.

123
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:32,040
Rise.

124
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:35,330
Pay respect again.

125
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:39,730
Rise.

126
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:42,330
Pay respect again.

127
00:11:43,770 --> 00:11:46,090
Rise.

128
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:50,420
Rites completed.

129
00:11:55,370 --> 00:11:59,690
My Lord, the offerings are blessed by the ancestors now.

130
00:11:59,690 --> 00:12:02,120
Eating them brings good luck.

131
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:19,870
My Lord,

132
00:12:19,870 --> 00:12:22,380
these desserts have been left outside for a long time.

133
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:24,220
They must be covered in dust.

134
00:12:24,220 --> 00:12:26,790
Let them make some new ones.

135
00:12:26,790 --> 00:12:29,440
Wrap the incense ash up and bury it at home.

136
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:31,570
It also brings good luck.

137
00:12:31,570 --> 00:12:33,780
Let's do as you say.

138
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,720
Where did this flower come from?

139
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,690
I have no idea.

140
00:12:40,690 --> 00:12:44,700
My Lady, is there anything wrong with this flower?

141
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,510
Why are you asking?

142
00:12:46,510 --> 00:12:48,950
- Throw it away. 
 - Understood.

143
00:12:52,220 --> 00:12:53,800
Father.

144
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:56,710
What now?

145
00:12:57,630 --> 00:13:00,030
You haven't visited my mother for so long.

146
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:04,230
You haven't visited her ever since she passed away.

147
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:07,870
I'm going to the hunting ground later.

148
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:11,440
You don't like hunting, so go ahead and visit your mother.

149
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,800
Zhifu, see that?

150
00:14:05,420 --> 00:14:08,380
I must retrieve it today.

151
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:25,210
- You two, go check. 
  - Father! 

152
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,120
Nice shot.

153
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:34,090
Why are you here? I thought you didn't like hunting.

154
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:38,330
You taught me archery when I was a child. I haven't forgotten it.

155
00:14:38,330 --> 00:14:41,000
You indulge in pleasure and never practice.

156
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:43,660
Come with us since you're here.

157
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:49,210
Father.

158
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:55,030
I saw a little deer heading in that direction.

159
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:56,710
I'll take a look.

160
00:15:06,020 --> 00:15:08,200
 Father! 

161
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,050
What's wrong?

162
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:27,610
   

163
00:15:27,610 --> 00:15:29,760
What are you doing?

164
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,840
You won't come to see my mother.

165
00:15:36,840 --> 00:15:40,150
I had no choice but to lure you here.

166
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:42,630
Don't you miss her at all?

167
00:15:42,630 --> 00:15:45,210
Don't you want to see her?

168
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:48,150
You loved and cared for her so much.

169
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:50,560
Why have you changed?

170
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:53,120
Why has everything changed?

171
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:58,950
It pains me to think about her.

172
00:15:58,950 --> 00:16:05,430
So, I'd rather not think about her or visit her.

173
00:16:05,430 --> 00:16:08,710
Do you still feel sad for her?

174
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:12,950
Enough. Let's go back.

175
00:16:12,950 --> 00:16:15,210
Father, wait!

176
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,630
The flowers are blooming on Mother's grave.

177
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:23,750
Please take them back and keep them in the vase.

178
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:29,060
If she misses you, perhaps she can see you through these flowers.

179
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:32,750
I'm sure she misses you a lot.

180
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:36,240
The talk of the spirits is all nonsense.

181
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:39,390
We martial arts practitioners don't believe that.

182
00:16:39,390 --> 00:16:41,720
No matter what, they bloomed on my mother's grave.

183
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:44,870
At least, bring them home for decoration.

184
00:16:53,870 --> 00:16:58,830
A real man shouldn't be obsessed with flowers.

185
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:08,510
You missed your mother a lot today.

186
00:17:08,510 --> 00:17:11,130
I won't scold you for that.

187
00:17:11,130 --> 00:17:14,290
It's getting late. Let's go.

188
00:17:24,460 --> 00:17:28,851
   

189
00:18:08,270 --> 00:18:10,980
You put the flowers there, didn't you?

190
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:17,270
Speculation is groundless. It's better to see it with your own eyes.

191
00:18:47,030 --> 00:18:51,870
Your mother was buried outside of the mausoleum without an outer coffin.

192
00:18:51,870 --> 00:18:55,690
That's why the coffin decayed so fast.

193
00:18:56,880 --> 00:19:02,630
The status of the living ones is demonstrated through chariots, robes, and estates.

194
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:09,110
That of the deceased is shown through coffins, shrouds, and graves.

195
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:15,480
It's hard to imagine that the Marquis's wife was buried like this.

196
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:25,950
I'm going to open it. Wait for me up there if you can't bear to see it.

197
00:19:25,950 --> 00:19:27,660
No need.

198
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:32,430
This is my mother.

199
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:39,480
Come on. Three, two, one.

200
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,790
Your mother's wrist bones are deformed

201
00:20:21,790 --> 00:20:25,920
and obviously thinner than the ones of ordinary people.

202
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:29,400
The carpal bones of her left hand are also deformed.

203
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:32,230
Before she died, had she experienced weakness,

204
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:36,120
dizziness, headaches, and numbness in the limbs?

205
00:20:39,110 --> 00:20:43,540
At first, she was just dizzy and drowsy.

206
00:20:43,540 --> 00:20:45,450
The physicians couldn't do much.

207
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:49,270
Then things got worse and worse.

208
00:20:49,270 --> 00:20:53,310
She was dizzy, nauseous, and listless all day long.

209
00:20:53,310 --> 00:20:55,230
In the end,

210
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:59,310
she was mumbling nonsense,

211
00:20:59,310 --> 00:21:03,030
having convulsions, and suffering unbearable pain.

212
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:06,160
That's right.

213
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:08,920
These symptoms point to Solitary South Star poisoning.

214
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:12,790
Those who are poisoned by that flower have something in common.

215
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:15,720
Their bones shrink and deform.

216
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:19,240
Besides, your mother was mumbling nonsense.

217
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:23,860
That's a sign of severe intoxication as the poison affects the brain.

218
00:21:25,510 --> 00:21:27,220
Are you sure?

219
00:21:29,140 --> 00:21:31,720
I've been learning from my master since childhood.

220
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:33,720
I can't be mistaken.

221
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:37,880
I think your mother passed away

222
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:40,480
with some seeds left undigested.

223
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:41,920
As time went by,

224
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:45,270
the seeds got into the soil with the corpse liquid

225
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:47,620
and took root to sprout.

226
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:52,220
My mother was the kindest person...

227
00:21:53,070 --> 00:21:55,700
who always endured everything.

228
00:21:56,450 --> 00:21:57,580
Why?

229
00:21:57,580 --> 00:21:59,050
Why?

230
00:22:00,130 --> 00:22:01,570
Why?

231
00:22:03,890 --> 00:22:09,000
One does not need to be evil to invite disaster.

232
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:13,350
This poison can't kill anyone overnight.

233
00:22:13,350 --> 00:22:18,330
It only erupts when it accumulates to a certain extent over time.

234
00:22:18,330 --> 00:22:23,000
That means the culprit was close to your mother.

235
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:27,750
Strangers couldn't have poisoned her little by little without being caught.

236
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:30,060
I told you to pay attention during the rites.

237
00:22:30,060 --> 00:22:31,810
What did you notice?

238
00:22:32,590 --> 00:22:34,440
Jiang Xiang.

239
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:37,790
What's the deal with that bunch of flowers in the mausoleum?

240
00:22:37,790 --> 00:22:43,260
I assume one of the ignorant maids made a mistake and put them there.

241
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:47,960
What an ignorant girl.

242
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:50,300
Find her and kill her.

243
00:22:50,300 --> 00:22:51,820
Understood.

244
00:22:51,820 --> 00:22:55,310
But it must have been a coincidence.

245
00:22:55,310 --> 00:22:57,400
Please don't be bothered, My Lady.

246
00:22:57,400 --> 00:23:00,260
I really hope it was just a coincidence.

247
00:23:01,350 --> 00:23:03,860
I'm afraid someone must have done it on purpose.

248
00:23:05,310 --> 00:23:09,880
Are you saying... that the second young master did it?

249
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:15,460
Do you think that he's suspecting something?

250
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:19,140
I don't think so.

251
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:23,550
He comes to the mausoleum in a disheveled manner every year

252
00:23:23,550 --> 00:23:26,070
and it's the same this time.

253
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:27,880
There's nothing different.

254
00:23:27,900 --> 00:23:31,900
If he had found out the truth, he would have made a big fuss about it.

255
00:23:31,900 --> 00:23:34,320
He wouldn't remain silent.

256
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:42,550
Besides, so what if he found out about it?

257
00:23:42,550 --> 00:23:44,240
He has no proof.

258
00:23:44,240 --> 00:23:48,850
And he's too much of a loser to cause you any trouble.

259
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:53,870
My Lady, you're truly farsighted to make him a good-for-nothing.

260
00:23:57,020 --> 00:23:59,690
She was in charge of the food and supplies.

261
00:23:59,690 --> 00:24:03,790
And my mother fell ill one year after she returned to the capital.

262
00:24:03,790 --> 00:24:09,260
 Zengzi said, "How profound indeed is the virtue of filial piety!" 

263
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,770
 You write so well, Xing'er. 

264
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:20,400
 Mother, are you all right? 

